# iOS-Specific Development Rules
# Last Updated: 2024-04-10

## iOS Development Guidelines

### StoreKit Integration
- Use StoreKit 2 for in-app purchases
- Implement proper receipt validation
- Handle subscription status updates
- Test with StoreKit configuration files
- Support family sharing if applicable

### iOS-Specific Features
- Implement proper memory management
- Handle iOS lifecycle events
- Support iOS-specific gestures
- Implement proper keyboard handling
- Support Dynamic Type

### UI Guidelines
- Follow iOS Human Interface Guidelines
- Support Safe Area insets
- Implement proper Dark Mode
- Handle different screen sizes
- Support accessibility features

### Performance
- Optimize memory usage
- Handle background/foreground transitions
- Implement proper caching
- Optimize image loading
- Handle low memory warnings

### Testing
- Use XCTest framework
- Implement UI tests
- Test in-app purchases
- Test different iOS versions
- Test on various devices

### App Store
- Follow App Store guidelines
- Prepare proper screenshots
- Write clear app descriptions
- Handle review process requirements
- Keep privacy labels up-to-date

### Security
- Implement proper keychain usage
- Handle sensitive data securely
- Use proper encryption
- Follow Apple's security guidelines
- Implement proper authentication 